22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20photo%20of%20a%20family%20of%205%20at%20a%20beach%20on%20a%20clear%2C%20sunny%20day.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65bc70cd7a3d27148876f7e1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222268%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EKaylee%20Massey%20and%20her%20family.%3Cp%3EKaylee%20Massey%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EKaylee%20Massey's%20youngest%20daughter%20Poppy%20was%20diagnosed%20with%20a%20rare%20genetic%20disorder%20at%20nine%20months%20old.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EPoppy%20died%20at%2015%20months%20old%20after%20being%20admitted%20into%20the%20hospital%20for%20an%20infection.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAfter%20the%20funeral%2C%20Kaylee%20and%20her%20husband%20Jake%20decided%20to%20turn%20Poppy's%20ashes%20into%20stones%20that%20they%20could%20keep%20at%20home.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Kaylee%20Massey%2C%20who%20runs%20a%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tiktok.com%2F%40poppy_and_kaylee%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ETikTok%20account%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20dedicated%20to%20her%20daughter.%20She%20posts%20about%20her%20life%20as%20a%20mother%20and%20shares%20her%20journey%20dealing%20with%20grief.%20This%20essay%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20our%20daughter%20Poppy%20was%20born%20in%20February%202022%2C%20we%20had%20no%20idea%20anything%20was%20wrong%20with%20her%20brain.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20my%20husband%2C%20Jake%2C%20and%20our%20two%20older%20children%2C%20Rosie%2C%208%2C%20and%20Peter%2C%206%2C%20we%20were%20this%20perfect%20little%20family%20of%20five%20for%20a%20few%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20right%20around%20the%20three-%20or%20four-month%20mark%2C%20we%20noticed%20Poppy's%20vision%20wasn't%20developing%20properly.%20She%20couldn't%20engage%20with%20eye%20contact%20or%20reach%20for%20toys.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Two%20older%20kids%20lying%20on%20the%20floor%20next%20to%20an%20infanct.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65bc92a26fcb546d2d4b737e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222268%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERosie%2C%20Peter%2C%20and%20Poppy.%3Cp%3EKaylee%20Massey%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20ophthalmologist%20couldn't%20tell%20us%20about%20what%20was%20causing%20the%20problem.%20We%20thought%20she'd%20get%20some%20little%20adorable%20baby%20glasses%2C%20that's%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20a%20few%20doctor%20appointments%2C%20we%20decided%20to%20get%20her%20an%20MRI%20and%20do%20a%20genetic%20test.%20The%20results%20of%20the%20test%20were%20devastating%3A%20Poppy%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftbcdfoundation.org%2Fabout-tbcd%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETBCD%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20rare%20and%20severe%20genetic%20disorder%20that%20affected%20her%20brain%20and%20spinal%20cord.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20were%20told%20her%20life%20expectancy%20was%20between%20three%20to%20five%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EBut%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20are%20both%20optimistic%20people%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20told%20ourselves%20that%20we'd%20give%20her%20the%20best%20care%20and%20that%20we'd%20be%20able%20to%20overcome%20this%20as%20a%20family.%20We%20were%20both%20thinking%20she'd%20easily%20hit%20the%20five-year%20mark%2C%20or%20even%20longer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20kept%20us%20afloat%20was%20just%20the%20busyness%20of%20the%20day-to-day.%20There%20wasn't%20much%20time%20to%20be%20devastated%20because%20we%20were%20moving%20forward.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20late%20April%2C%20we%20brought%20Poppy%20to%20the%20hospital%20because%20we%20noticed%20there%20was%20some%20blood%20in%20her%20feeding%20tube.%20The%20doctors%20found%20some%20spots%20of%20pneumonia%20in%20her%20lungs%2C%20and%20she%20continued%20to%20have%20a%20fever%20and%20seizures.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20medical%20team%20took%20great%20care%20of%20her.%20We%20didn't%20expect%20her%20condition%20to%20take%20a%20turn%20so%20quickly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20fourth%20night%20we%20were%20in%20the%20hospital%2C%20the%20medical%20team%20suggested%20we%20transfer%20Poppy%20to%20the%20pediatric%20ICU.%20As%20she%20was%20wheeled%20into%20her%20new%20room%2C%20her%20eyes%20suddenly%20looked%20up%20at%20us.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20remember%20saying%20something%20like%2C%20%26quot%3BOh%2C%20Poppy%2C%20you're%20awake.%26quot%3B%20And%20then%20her%20heart%20just%20stopped.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20entire%20room%20was%20thrown%20into%20chaos.%20I%20felt%20like%20my%20vision%20almost%20disappeared%2C%20and%20the%20room%20was%20spinning%20around%20me%20in%20slow%20motion%20as%20they%20tried%20to%20resuscitate%20our%20daughter.%20It%20was%20so%20traumatic%20to%20watch.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20got%20her%20heartbeat%20back%2C%20but%20her%20brain%20had%20been%20without%20oxygen%20for%20a%20decent%20amount%20of%20time.%20It%20was%20at%20the%20point%20where%20she%20would%20no%20longer%20experience%20any%20sort%20of%20quality%20of%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe're%20so%20grateful%20to%20her%20doctors%20who%20immediately%20started%20forming%20a%20care%20plan%2C%20but%20we%20already%20knew%20that%20it%20would%20be%20Poppy's%20last%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERosie%20and%20Peter%20came%20to%20the%20hospital%20that%20day.%20Our%20parents%20came%20too.%20We%20had%20a%20chance%20to%20say%20our%20goodbyes%20as%20a%20family%2C%20which%20I'll%20always%20be%20thankful%20for.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20hardest%20thing%20in%20the%20entire%20world%20was%20having%20to%20walk%20away%20from%20her%20body%20in%20the%20hospital%2C%20so%20we%20knew%20that%20we%20wanted%20Poppy's%20remains%20at%20home%20with%20us.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWe%20decided%20to%20have%20her%20ashes%20pressed%20into%20stones%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20we%20were%20looking%20through%20a%20catalog%20at%20the%20funeral%20home%2C%20that%20option%20stood%20out%20to%20us%20because%20we%20were%20concerned%20about%20having%20an%20urn%20in%20the%20house.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20didn't%20want%20our%20kids%20to%20associate%20a%20fear%20of%20breaking%20something%20with%20being%20close%20to%20their%20sister.%20Neither%20did%20we%20want%20them%20to%20feel%20like%20there%20was%20a%20shrine%20that%20they%20couldn't%20interact%20with.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20these%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeet-founder-parting-stone-turning-cremated-ashes-into-stones-2022-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estones%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20essentially%20unbreakable.%20In%20the%20future%2C%20if%20we%20wanted%20to%2C%20we%20could%20even%20take%20a%20stone%20with%20us%20wherever%20we%20go.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20whole%20process%20took%20about%20three%20months.%20It%20was%20an%20emotional%20day%20when%20her%20remains%20were%20back%20in%20our%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Twelve%20small%20white%20stones.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65bc908e43bb77284ba2e099%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222268%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPoppy's%20ashes%20produced%20about%2012%20small%20white%20stones%20with%20yellow%20specks.%3Cp%3EKaylee%20Massey%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20surprised%20us%20was%20how%20few%20stones%20there%20were%3A%20Poppy's%20ashes%20produced%20about%2012%20stones%20of%20varying%20sizes%2C%20and%20they%20were%20all%20quite%20small.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20say%20they%20don't%20add%20anything%20to%20the%20ashes%2C%20but%20when%20we%20opened%20the%20box%2C%20we%20noticed%20these%20little%20specks%20of%20yellow%20mixed%20into%20the%20white%20stone.%20I%20don't%20know%20what%20they%20are%2C%20but%20these%20little%20yellow%20specks%20make%20me%20smile%20whenever%20I%20see%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20kept%20the%20stones%20in%20the%20box%20they%20came%20in%20and%20placed%20the%20box%20on%20Poppy's%20swing%20in%20our%20kitchen.%20It%20was%20where%20she%20was%20whenever%20she%20wasn't%20in%20our%20arms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20small%20wooden%20box%20placed%20in%20a%20baby%20swing.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65bc916b6fcb546d2d4b735c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222268%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWe%20kept%20the%20stones%20in%20the%20box%20they%20came%20in%20and%20placed%20the%20box%20on%20Poppy's%20swing%20in%20our%20kitchen.%3Cp%3EKaylee%20Massey%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3EIt%20has%20been%20a%20beautiful%20thing%20for%20our%20family%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20a%20way%20to%20hold%20space%20for%20Poppy%20in%20our%20house.%20And%20the%20kids%20are%20not%20fearful%20of%20the%20stones.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20were%20quite%20direct%20with%20them%20about%20Poppy%20being%20cremated%2C%20and%20they%20both%20understand%20that%20these%20stones%20are%20compressed%20ashes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20kids%20don't%20play%20with%20them%2C%20but%20Peter%20will%20take%20them%20out%20more%20than%20Rosie.%20He'll%20hold%20one%20and%20walk%20around%20for%20a%20few%20minutes.%20When%20he's%20done%2C%20he'll%20put%20the%20stone%20back%20in%20the%20bag%20and%20close%20the%20box.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20think%20the%20stones%20helped%20me%20with%20my%20grief%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20spent%20the%2015%20months%20of%20Poppy's%20life%20working%20so%20hard%20to%20protect%20her.%20We%20would%20obviously%20choose%20to%20do%20that%20forever%2C%20but%20it%20almost%20feels%20like%20we%20can%20rest%20with%20Poppy%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20much%20was%20changing%20so%20fast%20while%20she%20was%20alive%2C%20but%20the%20stones%20feel%20like%20permanence%2C%20and%20there's%20something%20symbolic%20about%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESteady%20as%20a%20rock%2C%20and%20that%20gives%20me%20a%20lot%20of%20comfort.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22h