%20budget%2C%20it%20has%20increased%20to%20just%20Rs.%201%2C21%2C022.85%20crore%20in%20the%20current%20budget.%20There%20are%20also%20often%20repeated%20cases%20of%20underutilisation%20of%20funds%20in%20the%20given%20fiscal%20year.%20For%20instance%2C%20the%20Revised%20Estimates%20for%202023-24%20reveal%20that%20expenditures%20reduced%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fbusiness%2Fbudget%2Fin-interim-budget-estimates-for-social-justice-and-tribal-affairs-ministries-see-marginal-increase%2Farticle67800764.ece%5C%22%3E23%25%20and%2038%25%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0for%20the%20Social%20Justice%20Ministry%20and%20the%20Tribal%20Affairs%20Ministry%20respectively.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20shows%20that%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Social%20Justice%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fbusiness%2Fbudget%2Fin-interim-budget-estimates-for-social-justice-and-tribal-affairs-ministries-see-marginal-increase%2Farticle67800764.ece%5C%22%3Enot%20able%20to%20spend%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20budget%20allocated%20to%20the%20SEED%20scheme%2C%20while%20the%20tribal%20affairs%20ministry%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pressreader.com%2Findia%2Fthe-hindu-tiruchirapalli-9WWf%2F20240202%2F282071986791075%5C%22%3Efell%20short%20of%20spending%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20its%20flagship%20project%20Eklavya%20Model%20Residential%20Schools%20(EMRS).%20The%20revised%20estimates%20for%20the%20SEED%20scheme%20for%202023-24%20are%20only%20Rs%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiabudget.gov.in%2Fdoc%2Feb%2Fsbe93.pdf%5C%22%3E15%20crore%20although%20the%20allocation%20was%20Rs%2040%20crore%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Whenever%20there%20are%20large%20revisions%20in%20the%20budget%2C%20it%20not%20only%20affects%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiaspend.com%2Fbudget%2Fbe-re-or-actuals-what-do-you-need-to-look-at-in-the-upcoming-budget-800937%5C%22%3Ecredibility%20of%20numbers%3C%2Fa%3E%20presented%20in%20the%20budget%2C%20but%20the%20downward%20revisions%2C%20in%20particular%2C%20can%20be%20unfavourable%20for%20beneficiaries%20who%20are%20likely%20to%20receive%20fewer%20benefits%20and%20the%20benefits%20may%20also%20get%20restricted%20to%20fewer%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20SEED%20scheme%20was%20launched%20in%20February%202022%20for%20the%20economic%20empowerment%20of%20Denotified%20(DNT)%2C%20Nomadic%20(NT)%20and%20Semi-nomadic%20tribes%20(SNT).%20The%20scheme%20aims%20to%20provide%20livelihood%20support%2C%20health%20insurance%2C%20assistance%20for%20housing%2C%20and%20competitive%20exam%20coaching.%20Though%20quite%20comprehensive%20in%20its%20scope%2C%20the%20scheme%20has%20failed%20to%20deliver.%20While%20the%20Social%20Justice%20ministry%20received%20nearly%205%2C400%20online%20applications%20for%20availing%20the%20benefits%20under%20the%20scheme%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fexpedite-categorisation-of-denotified-nomadic-semi-nomadic-tribes-house-panel%2Farticle66307303.ece%5C%22%3Enone%20of%20the%20applications%20had%20been%20approved%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20portal%20citing%20reasons%20of%20tribe%20categorisation%20into%20SC%2C%20ST%20and%20OBCs%20for%20the%20delay%20in%20implementation.%20Looking%20at%20the%20under-utilisation%20of%20funds%2C%20it%20appears%20that%20not%20much%20improvement%20has%20happened%20on%20that%20front.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPM%20Narendra%20Modi%20in%20his%20Lok%20Sabha%20address%20on%20February%205%20claimed%20that%20his%20government%20has%20taken%20up%20the%20welfare%20of%20the%20most%20vulnerable%20people%20of%20the%20country%20on%20a%20mission%20mode.%20The%20prime%20minister%20took%20credit%20for%20recognising%20the%20Particularly%20Vulnerable%20Tribal%20Groups%20(PVTGs)%20who%20are%20otherwise%20rendered%20invisible%20in%20the%20vote%20bank%20politics%20due%20to%20their%20small%20numbers%20in%20the%20population.%20He%20referred%20to%20the%20introduction%20of%20the%20PM%20JANMAN%20scheme%20as%20a%20testimony%20of%20his%20government%E2%80%99s%20commitment%20to%20the%20cause%20of%20tribal%20welfare.%20However%2C%20the%20recent%20allocations%20in%20the%20interim%20budget%202024-25%2C%20do%20not%20match%20these%20claims%20and%20certainly%20do%20not%20the%20findings%20of%20various%20reports%20on%20the%20socioeconomic%20status%20of%20the%20marginalised%20groups.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20Tribal%20Development%20Report%2C%202022%2C%20the%20first%20of%20its%20kind%20since%20independence%2C%20Adivasis%20are%20at%20the%20bottom%20rung%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20development%20pyramid.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Frchiips.org%2Fnfhs%2FNFHS-5Reports%2FNFHS-5_INDIA_REPORT.pdf%5C%22%3ENational%20Family%20Health%20Survey-5%3C%2Fa%3E%20(2019-21)%20clearly%20indicates%20that%20over%2070%20per%20cent%20of%20Scheduled%20Tribes%20lie%20in%20the%20lowest%20quintiles.%20Likewise%2C%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Tribal%20Affairs%20(MoTA)%20in%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftribal.nic.in%2Fdownloads%2FStatistics%2FAnnualReport%2FAREnglish2122.pdf%5C%22%3E2021-22%20Annual%20Report%3C%2Fa%3E%20reveals%20that%20over%2045%25%20of%20STs%20were%20living%20below%20the%20poverty%20line%20in%20rural%20areas%20and%20over%2025%25%20in%20urban%20areas.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20would%2C%20therefore%2C%20make%20better%20sense%20to%20look%20at%20development%20indicators%20such%20as%20education%2C%20health%20and%20nutrition%20as%20analytical%20screens%20against%20absolute%20budget%20numbers%20or%20percentage%20increases%20under%20various%20schemes%20for%20these%20marginalised%20sections%20of%20society.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20NHFS-5%2C%20the%20median%20years%20of%20schooling%20completed%20for%20STs%20was%20a%20mere%205.2%20as%20compared%20to%208.5%20of%20the%20socially%20dominant%20%E2%80%98other%E2%80%99%20category.%20Likewise%2C%20the%20school%20attendance%20ratio%20(65.1%25)%20was%20the%20lowest%20for%20STs%20in%20the%20middle%2C%20secondary%20and%20higher%20secondary%20education%20sector.%20The%20Union%20Budget%202024-25%20remains%20flat-footed%20in%20assessing%20the%20educational%20needs%20of%20these%20communities%20with%20a%20discernable%20reduction%20in%20budget%20allocation%20for%20scholarships%20and%20fellowships.%20For%20instance%2C%20the%20PM%20Research%20Fellowship%20under%20AWST%20witnesses%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen.themooknayak.com%2Feducation%2Fmarginalized-students-disappointed-by-budget-cuts-in-scholarships-and-fellowships%5C%22%3Edecrease%20from%20Rs.%2034%20crores%20to%20Rs.%2030%20crore%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20Rs.%2030%20crore%20under%20AWST%2C%20down%20from%20Rs.%2034%20crore.%20The%20overall%20budgetary%20allocation%20on%20education%20needs%20to%20be%20brought%20in%20line%20with%20the%20recommendations%20of%20National%20Education%20Policy%202020%20which%20advocates%206%25%20of%20GDP%20to%20be%20spent%20on%20the%20sector.%20This%20comes%20to%20Rs%2019%2C66%2C309%20crore%2C%20but%20in%20the%20current%20budget%2C%20education%20was%20allocated%20Rs%201%2C24%2C638%20crore.%20The%20interim%20budget%202024-25%20shows%20no%20effort%20has%20been%20made%20to%20ensure%20quality%20education%20for%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInclusive%20development%20cannot%20be%20achieved%20without%20securing%20the%20health%20and%20nutrition%20needs%20of%20the%20Scheduled%20Tribes.%20The%20infant%20mortality%20rate%20for%20Scheduled%20Tribes%20was%20over%2041%20compared%20to%2028%20for%20all%3B%20the%20under-five%20mortality%20rate%20was%2050%20for%20Scheduled%20Tribes%20and%2033%20for%20all%2C%20according%20to%20the%20NFHS-5.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Rural%20Health%20Statistics%20(2021-22)%20revealed%20a%20shortfall%20of%209357%20sub-centres%2C%201559%20primary%20health%20centres%20and%20372%20community%20health%20centres%20in%20tribal%20areas%20against%20the%20required%20numbers%20as%20on%C2%A0%20March%2031%2C%202022.%20NFHS-5%20also%20reports%20the%20Nutritional%20Status%20of%20Children%20and%20revealed%20that%20over%2040%25%20of%20ST%20children%20were%20stunted%2C%2023%25%20were%20wasted%20and%20about%2039%20were%20underweight%20compared%20to%20%E2%80%98Other%E2%80%99%20communities%20at%2030%25%2C%2017.5%25%2C%20and%2027%25%2C%20respectively.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGiven%20the%20depravity%20of%20the%20educational%20and%20health%20conditions%20of%20these%20marginalised%20sections%20of%20society%2C%20the%20interim%20Union%20Budget%202024-25%20is%20a%20statement%20of%20apathy%20and%20indifference%20beneath%20the%20claims%20of%20inclusivity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EK.C.%20Adaina%20and%20Divya%20Pradeep%20teach%20Economics%20at%20Azim%20Premji%20University%20and%20Christ%20University%2C%20Bangalore%2C%20respectively.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707568247000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F08%2F12153912%2F4571749931_deb5b2597f_o.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fthe-interim-budget-is-indifferent-to-the-concerns-of-adivasis%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20estimates%20presented%20by%20finance%20minister%20for%20FY%202024-25%20for%20Social%20Justice%20and%20Tribal%20Affairs%20Ministries%20remained%20largely%20unchanged%20and%20see%20a%20marginal%20increase%20of%201%25%20in%20its%20allocation%20across%20all%20schemes%20for%20STs.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fthe-interim-budget-is-indifferent-to-the-concerns-of-adivasis%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Free%20AFC%20Asian%20Cup%20final%20live%20stream%3A%20How%20to%20watch%20Qatar%20vs.%20Jordan%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EWhen%20you%20buy%20through%20our%20links%2C%20Business%20Insider%20may%20earn%20an%20affiliate%20commission.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Finsider-reviews-expertise-in-product-reviews%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELearn%20more%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223156%5C%22%20al