ant.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAdopting%20a%20retainer-based%20model%20increased%20Morassutti's%20earnings%20and%20allowed%20for%20a%20more%20flexible%20schedule.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EShe%20made%20six%20figures%20last%20year%20and%20is%20using%20skills%20learned%20from%20clients%20to%20start%20her%20own%20business.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20is%20an%20as-told-to%20story%20with%20Rebecca%20Morassutti%2C%20a%20virtual%20assistant.%20Morassutti%E2%80%99s%20income%20has%20been%20verified%20by%20Business%20Insider.%20The%20following%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20clarity%20and%20length.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20climbed%20the%20corporate%20ladder%20in%20a%20large%20multinational%20company%20from%20intern%20to%20associate%20director%20within%20a%20few%20years.%20In%202011%2C%20my%20friends%20and%20family%20thought%20I%20was%20living%20the%20dream%20%E2%80%94%20I%20had%20a%20nice%20car%2C%20a%20good%20salary%2C%20and%20a%20growing%20savings%20account.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20inside%2C%20I%20was%20stressed%20and%20burned%20out%20doing%20the%20job%20of%20three%20different%20people.%20I%20couldn't%20live%20like%20that%20for%20the%20next%2050%20years.%20I%20wanted%20to%20work%20remotely%20and%20have%20flexible%20hours%2C%20so%20I%20started%20thinking%20about%20starting%20an%20online%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20turned%20up%20my%20nose%20at%20virtual%20assisting%20at%20first%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EGoogling%20online%20businesses%20for%20digital%20nomads%20led%20me%20to%20virtual%20assistant%2C%20or%20VA%2C%20work.%20Initially%2C%20I%20turned%20my%20nose%20up%20at%20it.%20I%20felt%20like%20I%20was%20too%20experienced%20to%20be%20anyone%E2%80%99s%20assistant%20and%20worried%20people%20would%20say%20I%E2%80%99d%20taken%20a%20step%20down.%20It%20took%20until%202014%20to%20get%20past%20my%20fear%20of%20optics.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20breaking%20point%20was%20being%20denied%20a%202%25%20raise.%20The%20moment%20I%20got%20back%20to%20my%20desk%2C%20I%20started%20looking%20for%20any%20virtual%20assistant%20work%20I%20could%20do.%20Within%2024%20hours%2C%20I%20landed%20my%20first%20client%20on%20Upwork%20by%20submitting%20a%20proposal%20for%20a%20project.%20I%20still%20work%20with%20her%20almost%2010%20years%20later.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20doing%20business%20operations%20and%20client%20management%20for%20this%20client.%20I%20would%20wake%20up%20early%20to%20do%20her%20work%20and%20work%20on%20VA%20tasks%20during%20my%20lunch%20break.%20Anything%20I%20didn't%20get%20done%20during%20the%20day%2C%20I%20would%20do%20when%20I%20got%20home.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20month%20after%20working%20with%20her%2C%20I%20gave%20my%20three-month%20notice.%20I%20had%20a%20ballpark%20figure%20of%20the%20bare%20minimum%20income%20to%20cover%20my%20expenses.%20It%20took%20four%20months%20as%20a%20VA%20to%20work%20up%20to%20that.%20Luckily%2C%20my%20long%20notice%20period%20meant%20I%20could%20find%20more%20clients%20through%20Upwork%20and%20networking%20on%20LinkedIn%20while%20still%20having%20backup%20money%20coming%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20end%20of%20my%20first%20year%2C%20I%20made%20around%20%2465%2C000%20from%20VA%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20accidentally%20created%20another%20job%20for%20myself%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20few%20years%20in%20my%20VA%20business%2C%20I%20was%20happy%20to%20take%20any%20client.%20I%20quickly%20realized%20some%20clients%20didn't%20understand%20the%20role%20of%20a%20virtual%20assistant.%20They%20expected%20me%20to%20work%20specific%20hours%20and%20fixed%20availability.%20I%20still%20felt%20like%20an%20employee%20when%20I%20was%20supposed%20to%20be%20self-employed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%202016%2C%20I%20was%20burned%20out%20again.%20I%20felt%20like%20I%20had%20been%20lied%20to.%20Every%20post%20online%20discussed%20how%20being%20a%20VA%20was%20this%20path%20to%20poolside%20work%20and%20a%20flexible%20schedule.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ESwitching%20from%20hourly%20pay%20to%20a%20retainer%20increased%20my%20earnings%20as%20a%20VA%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202017%2C%20I%20considered%20returning%20to%20my%209-to-5%20job.%20I%20wanted%20to%20give%20up%20on%20entrepreneurship%20altogether.%20I%20stuck%20with%20it%20because%20I%20knew%20I%20was%20adding%20value%20to%20my%20client's%20businesses%20and%20even%20taking%20on%20leadership%20responsibilities%20for%20some%20clients.%20I%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20getting%20paid%20for%20taking%20on%20that%20responsibility%2C%20and%20I%20knew%20I%20needed%20to%20change%20my%20compensation%20model.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20more%20online%20research%2C%20I%20realized%20I%20needed%20to%20stop%20trading%20my%20time%20for%20money.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%2C%20if%20I%20got%20more%20efficient%20at%20doing%20a%20task%2C%20I%20was%20penalized.%20For%20example%2C%20scheduling%20an%20email%20may%20take%20me%2030%20minutes%20the%20first%20time%20I%20did%20it%2C%20but%20after%20a%20month%2C%20that%20time%20was%20down%20to%2015%20minutes.%20On%20an%20hourly%20rate%2C%20I%20would%20have%20to%20find%20something%20else%20to%20do%20to%20fill%20my%20time%20without%20extra%20pay.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20my%20new%20pricing%20model%2C%20I%20was%20paid%20on%20a%20retainer%20rather%20than%20hourly.%20This%20removed%20me%20from%20the%20time-to-money%20exchange.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20analyzed%20the%20value%20I%20added%20to%20my%20clients'%20businesses%20and%20presented%20them%20with%20a%20pricing%20structure%20based%20on%20that%20research.%20I%20used%20proof%20of%20sales%20from%20emails%20and%20campaigns%20I'd%20run.%20The%20bigger%20my%20revenue%20impact%2C%20the%20higher%20my%20retainer.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20lost%20some%20clients%2C%20but%20the%20ones%20who%20stayed%20were%20happy%20to%20pay%20more.%20With%20this%20new%20structure%2C%20I%20no%20longer%20kept%20track%20of%20my%20hours%20because%20I%20was%20on%20a%20retainer%2C%20so%20I%20could%20take%20time%20off%20without%20being%20pai