20of%20Washington%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20Gregory%20studied%20moving%20as%20part%20of%20the%20university's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdepts.washington.edu%2Fmoving1%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EAmerica%E2%80%99s%20Great%20Migrations%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20project.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20a%20much%20smaller%20share%20of%20Americans%20move%20each%20year.%20In%202022%2C%20the%20overall%20national%20migration%20rate%2C%20which%20tracks%20the%20ratio%20of%20movers%20in%20the%20US%20compared%20to%20the%20population%20aged%20one%20year%20and%20older%2C%20was%20just%2012.6%25%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.census.gov%2Flibrary%2Fstories%2F2023%2F11%2Fstate-to-state-migration.html%23%3A~%3Atext%3DBetween%25202021%2520and%25202022%252C%2520the%2C%252Dto%252Dstate%2520migration%2520flows.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ecensus%20data%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20almost%20half%20of%20what%20it%20once%20was%20during%20the%20heyday%20of%20American%20migration.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20deceleration%20in%20historical%20migration%20has%2C%20in%20part%2C%20been%20spurred%20by%20an%20increasingly%20robust%20job%20market%20that%20has%20given%20rise%20to%20more%20economic%20opportunities%2C%20bringing%20the%20idea%20of%20the%20American%20dream%20closer%20within%20reach%20than%20ever%20before.%C2%A0In%20short%2C%20people%20no%20longer%20need%20to%20move%20at%20such%20high%20rates%20in%20order%20to%20attain%20the%20job%20they%20desire%2C%20Gregory%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20while%20overall%20migration%20is%20nearly%20as%20low%20as%20it%E2%80%99s%20been%20in%2075%20years%2C%20big%20moves%20%E2%80%94%20ones%20that%20involve%20crossing%20state%20lines%20%E2%80%94%20are%20on%20the%20rise%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20from%20states%20like%20New%20York%20and%20California%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoving-to-florida-pros-cons-millennials-gen-x-retirement-census-2024-