y%20said.%20A%20burgeoning%20defense%20industry%20to%20support%20the%20war%20effort%20also%20created%20new%20jobs%20for%20Americans%2C%20which%20spurred%20moves.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20rate%20of%20migration%20slowed%20slightly%20following%20the%20end%20of%20the%20war%2C%20but%20a%20great%20industrial%20boom%20soon%20followed%2C%20resulting%20in%20massive%20movement%20to%20previously%20underdeveloped%20regions%20in%20the%20country%20that%20were%20building%20new%20factories%20and%20hiring%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224949%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20group%20of%20workers%20sit%20on%20a%20long%20bench%20having%20their%20lunch%20at%20the%20Chrysler%20Mound%20Road%20Engine%20factory%2C%20Detroit%2C%20Michigan%2C%20circa%201955.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65c53fb46fcb546d2d4daa21%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223967%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPeople%20flocked%20to%20cities%20like%20Detroit%20during%20industrialization%20for%20factory%20jobs.%3Cp%3EArchive%20Photos%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20American%20West%2C%20in%20particular%2C%20including%20California%2C%20Oregon%2C%20and%20Washington%2C%20saw%20migration%20en%20masse%20as%20those%20states%20became%20industrialized%20and%20people%20moved%20for%20new%20jobs%2C%20Gregory%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20major%20manufacturing%20hubs%20in%20the%20Midwest%2C%20like%20Detroit%2C%20continued%20to%20grow%20in%20size%20and%20scale%2C%20drawing%20lots%20of%20new%20residents%2C%20especially%20out%20of%20the%20South.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20trend%20continued%20into%20the%201960s%2C%20coinciding%20with%20the%20later%20stages%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.history.com%2Ftopics%2Fblack-history%2Fgreat-migration%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EGreat%20Migration%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20as%20Black%20Americans%20fled%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fphotos-seg