20The%20Brookings%20Institution%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EInternal%20migration%20has%20continued%20to%20slow%20since%C2%A0the%201970s%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Census%20Bureau%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.census.gov%2Ftopics%2Fpopulation%2Fmigration%2Fdata%2Ftables%2Fcps.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ecurrent%20population%20survey%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20tracked%20domestic%20movement%20every%20year%20since%20the%201947-1948%20cycle.%20According%20to%20the%20data%2C%20overall%20migration%20fell%20to%20about%2017%25%20in%20the%201980s%3B%20to%20about%2016%25%20in%20the%201990s%3B%20and%20to%20about%2014%25%20in%20the%20early%202000s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20takes%20money%20to%20move.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20Great%20Recession%20in%202008%20hobbled%20the%20economy%20and%20slowed%20migration%2C%20sending%20the%20overall%20rate%20to%2011%20or%2012%25%2C%20according%20to%20census%20data.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMore%20than%20a%20decade%20later%2C%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic%20slashed%20internal%20US%20migration%20even%20further.%20While%20the%20US%20Census%20didn't%20publish%20an%20official%20migration%20rate%20for%202020%20because%20of%20high%20rates%20of%20nonresponse%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.brookings.edu%2Farticles%2Famericans-local-migration-reached-a-historic-low-in-2022-but-long-distance-moves-picked-up%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBrookings%3C%2Fa%3E%20used%20several%20tabulations%20of%20various%20Census%20data%20to%20estimate%20the%20overall%20rate%20for%202020%20through%202021%20was%208.4%25%20%E2%80%94%20the%20lowest%20in%2075%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20country%20locked%20down%20and%20jobs%20increasingly%20went%20remote%2C%20people%20stayed%20home%20and%20stopped%20moving.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Home%20for%20sale%20sign%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64134f0a0308e000185513f6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223467%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3ELong-distance%20moves%20are%20on%20the%20up%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20overall%20migration%20rate%20is%20low%2C%20big%20moves%20are%20slowly%20on%20the%20rise.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECross-country%20moves%20from%20one%20state%20to%20another%2C%20like%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoving-to-texas-california-florida-new-york-housing-expensive-2023-10%23%3A~%3Atext%3DHere%2527s%2520where%2520they%2527re%2520moving.%26amp%3Btext%3DOver%2520100%252C000%2520Californians%2520made%2520the%2Creasons%2520for%2520making%2520the%2520move.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Etens%20of%20thousands%20of%20Californians%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20who%20fled%20the%20Golden%20State%20for%20Texas%20between%202021%20and%202022%2C%20are%20becoming%20more%20commonplace%2C%20according%20to%20census%20data%20and%20realtors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20American%20Community%20Survey%2C%20which%20tracks%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20changing%20demographics%2C%20found%20state-to-state%20movers%20comprised%20a%20larger%20share%20of%20all%20movers%20between%202021%20and%202022%2C%20with%20an%20increase%20from%2018.8%25%20to%2019.9%25%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.census.gov%2Flibrary%2Fstories%2F2023%2F11%2Fstate-to-state-migration.html%23%3A~%3Atext%3DBetween%25202021%2520and%25202022%252C%2520the%2C%252Dto%252Dstate%2520migration%2520flows.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ecensus%20data%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20About%208.2%20million%20people%20moved%20states%20in%202022%20%E2%80%94%20continuing%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.census.gov%2Fcontent%2Fdam%2FCensus%2Flibrary%2Fpublications%2F2023%2Facs%2Facs-53.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etrend%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20increasing%20state-to-state%20migration%20since%202006.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EAmericans%20are%2