.%20His%20pension%20from%20the%20police%20department%20was%20not%20enough%20to%20rent%20an%20apartment%20in%20California%2C%20and%20he%20knew%20he%20didn't%20want%20to%20un-retire.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20time%2C%20he%20had%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcouples-sold-their-homes-and-now-live-in-luxury-rvs-2022-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emotorhome%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20though%20he%20could%20drive%2C%20he%20couldn't%20handle%20other%20tasks%20like%20cleaning%20due%20to%20his%20disability.%20For%20a%20few%20months%2C%20he%20slept%20in%20his%20motorhome%20wherever%20he%20could%2C%20took%20showers%20at%20a%20gym%2C%20and%20camped%20out%20at%20coffee%20shops%20to%20get%20free%20WiFi.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20all%20got%20old%20really%20quick%2C%20so%20my%20only%20option%20was%20to%20move%20out%20of%20the%20country%20at%20that%20point%20because%20nowhere%20in%20the%20United%20States%20was%20I%20able%20to%20get%20an%20apartment%2C%26quot%3B%20Wiesmann%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20temporarily%20moved%20into%20an%20Airbnb%20in%20Mexico%2C%20moving%20around%20throughout%20the%20country.%20He%20stayed%20there%20for%20about%20six%20or%20seven%20months%2C%20staying%20at%20various%20Airbnbs%20in%20Cabo%20San%20Lucas%20in%20between%20short%20stays%20in%20California%20with%20friends%20and%20family.%20It%20cost%20him%20%241%2C000%20a%20month%20for%20his%20long-term%20studio%20rental%2C%20located%20a%20few%20blocks%20from%20the%20beach.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20spent%20much%20of%20his%20time%20on%20the%20beach%20or%20in%20caf%C3%A9s%20and%20got%20into%20photography.%20He%20said%20food%20costs%20weren't%20too%20expensive%2C%20though%20he%20still%20paid%20tourist%20prices%20for%20many%20daily%20expenses.%20He%20said%20he%20rarely%20felt%20isolated%20in%20Mexico%20and%20was%20able%20to%20navigate%20life%20in%20a%20new%20country%20rather%20smoothly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20February%202020%2C%20he%20relocated%20to%20Medell%C3%ADn%2C%20Colom