%2C%20the%20ministry%20carried%20out%20a%20public%20consultation%20seeking%20comments%20on%20the%20draft%20Bill.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeveral%20media%20bodies%20expressed%20consternation%20over%20the%20upcoming%20law.%20Journalist%20bodies%20%E2%80%93%20The%20National%20Alliance%20of%20Journalists%20(NAJ)%2C%20the%20Delhi%20Union%20of%20Journalists%20(DUJ)%2C%20and%20the%20Andhra%20Pradesh%20Working%20Journalists%20Federation%20(APWJF)%20join%20the%20Network%20of%20Women%20in%20Media%20India%2C%20(NWMI)%20and%20the%20Editors%20Guild%20of%20India%20and%20others%20%E2%80%93%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Fgateway-to-censorship-journalist-bodies-express-concern-over-proposed-broadcasting-services-bill%5C%22%3Ehave%20expressed%20%E2%80%9Cgrave%20reservations%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fa%3E%20against%20the%20proposed%20law.%20They%20describe%20it%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Cgateway%20to%20censorship%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20joint%20statement%20the%20NAJ%2C%20DUJ%2C%20and%20APWJF%20say%20that%20this%20proposed%20Bill%20is%20a%20step%20further%20%E2%80%9Cto%20expanding%20a%20new%20era%20of%20undeclared%20censorship%E2%80%9D%20and%20increasing%20government%20control%20over%20all%20types%20of%20media%20from%20TV%20channels%2C%20to%20films%2C%20and%20platforms%20like%20Netflix%20and%20Prime%20Video%2C%20YouTube%2C%20radio%2C%20even%20Instagram%20and%20other%20social%20media%20platforms%20as%20well%20as%20news%20websites%20and%20journalists.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Editors%20Guild%20of%20India%20(EGI)%20had%20written%20to%20Union%20information%20and%20broadcasting%20minister%20Anurag%20Thakur%20calling%20the%20draft%20of%20the%20Bill%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Fvague-and-excessively-intrusive-editors-guild-of-india-to-centre-on-broadcast-services-bill%5C%22%3Evague%20and%20excessively%20intrusive%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D.%20The%20EGI%2C%20whose%20mandate%20is%20to%20%E2%80%9Cprotect%20freedom%20of%20speech%20and%20to%20raise%20standards%20of%20editorial%20leadership%E2%80%9D%20of%20news%20media%20outlets%2C%20had%20told%20the%20minister%20that%20the%20new%20Bill%20will%20prove%20%E2%80%9Cadverse%20to%20the%20spirit%20of%20freedom%20of%20speech%20and%20freedom%20of%20the%20press%20guaranteed%20by%20the%20constitution%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fcontrol-all-or-delete-the-draft-broadcast-bill-is-a-blueprint-for-censorship%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%20earlier%20that%20%E2%80%9Cas%20a%C2%A0charter%20for%20censorship%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmib.gov.in%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2FPublic%2520Notice_0.pdf%5C%22%3Ethe%20Broadcasting%20Services%20(Regulation)%20Bill%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%20(Broadcast%20Bill)%20drafted%20by%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Information%20and%20Broadcasting%20(MIB)%20is%20a%20remarkable%20instrument%E2%80%A6%20this%20is%20an%20omnibus%20set%20of%20rules%20aimed%20at%20shutting%20down%20any%20news%20or%20views%20even%20mildly%20not%20in%20the%20service%20of%20those%20who%20happen%20to%20be%20in%20government%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707551036000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F10%2F23203159%2FScreen-Shot-2020-10-23-at-8.31.43-PM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fparliamentary-panel-tells-centre-to-expedite-passage-of-controversial-broadcasting-services-bill%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20parliamentary%20standing%20committee%20on%20communication%20and%20information%20technology%20said%20it%20would%20like%20to%20'engage%20in%20constructive%20discussions%20regarding%20the%20proposed%20draft%20legislation%20at%20a%20more%20mature%20stage%20of%20its%20formulation'.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fparliamentary-panel-tells-centre-to-expedite-passage-of-controversial-broadcasting-services-bill%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Fighter%20earns%20its%20lowest%20collection%20on%20Friday%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707550548000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-107577871%2Cimgsize-48934.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fbox-office%2Ffighter-earns-its-lowest-collection-on-third-friday-mints-only-rs-1-75-crore%2Farticleshow%2F107577914.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F107577914.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EHrithik%20Roshan%20and%20Deepika%20Padukone's%20%26quot%3BFighter%26quot%3B%20witnessed%20a%20decline%20in%20box%20office%20earnings%2C%20earning%20only%20Rs%201.75%20crore%20on%20its%20third%20Friday.%20Despite%20a%20promising%20second%20weekend%2C%20it%20struggled%20in%20the%20weekdays.%20Facing%20competition%2C%20the%20film's%20total%20collection%20stands%20at%20Rs%20189.25%20crore%2C%20with%20audience%20feedback%20citing%20a%20lack%20of%20novelty.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Imran%20Khan%2C%20Nawaz%20Sharif%2C%20Bilawal%20Bhutto%20Fight%20In%20Pak's%20Game%20Of%20Thrones%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Col%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EBut%20after%20long%20delays%20in%20results%20that%20prompted%20further%20allegations%20the%20military%20had%20engaged%20in%20vote-rigging%2C%20the%20army-backed%20Pakistan%20Muslim%20League-Nawaz%20(PML-N)%20declared%20victory%20as%20the%20party%20with%20the%20largest%20number%20of%20seats.%20However%2C%20to%20form%20a%20government%2C%20the%20party%20founded%20by%20the%20three-time%20former%20Prime%20Minister%20Nawaz%20Sharif%20will%20be%20forced%20to%20cut%20deals%20with%20rivals%20and%20independents.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20PPP%2C%20whose%20popularity%20is%20largely%20limited%20to%20its%20Sindh%20heartland%2C%20also%20did%20better%20than%20expected%2C%20with%20leader%20Bilawal%20Bhutto%20Zardari%20saying%20early%20results%20were%20%26quot%3Bvery%20encouraging%26quot%3B.%20The%20PML-N%20and%20PPP%20joined%20forces%20with%20minor%20parties%20to%20boot%20Khan%20from%20office%20in%20April%202022%20after%20his%20PTI%20had%20won%20a%20slender%20majority%20in%20the%202018%20election.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%26quot%3BWe%20don't%20have%20enough%20of%20a%20majority%20to%20run%20the%20government%20ourselves%2C%20therefore%20we%20invite%20the%20other%20parties%20and%20candidates%20who%20have%20been%20successful%20to%20work%20with%20us%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Sharif%20said%20at%20his%20party%20headquarters%20in%20Lahore.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EImran%20Khan%20yesterday%20claimed%20victory%20in%20the%20general%20election%20in%20an%20audio-visual%20message%20created%20using%20artificial%20intelligence%20and%20shared%20on%20his%20X%20social%20media%20account.%20Imran%20Khan%20heads%20the%20Pakistan%20Tehreek-e-Insaf%20(PTI).%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20PTI%20had%20defied%20a%20months-long%20crackdown%20that%20crippled%20campaigning%20and%20forced%20their%20candidates%20to%20run%20as%20independents%20with%20a%20combined%20showing%20in%20Thursday's%20election%20that%20still%20challenged%20their%20chief%20rivals.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EImran%20Khan%20also%20rejected%20rival%20Nawaz%20Sharif's%20earlier%20claim%20to%20victory.%20Khan%20called%20on%20his%20supporters%20to%20celebrate%20a%20win%20that%20was%20achieved%20despite%20what%20he%20calls%20a%20crackdown%20on%20his%20party.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EA%20slow%20counting%20process%20showed%20independents%20had%20won%20at%20least%2099%20seats%20--%2088%20of%20them%20loyal%20to%20Khan%20--%20by%20Saturday%20morning.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EPML-N%20took%2071%20and%20the%20Pakistan%20Peoples%20Party%20(PPP)%20snapped%20up%2053%2C%20with%2015%20of%20the%20