khan-in-pakistan-election-2024-5030321%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22K.%20Balagopal%E2%80%99s%20Incisive%20Essays%20on%20Caste%2C%20Communalism%20and%20Rise%20of%20State%20Authoritarianism%20in%20India%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F30123722%2FIllustration-Pariplab-Chakraborty.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EK.%20Balagopal%20was%20a%20civil%20rights%20activist%20and%20left-wing%20intellectual%20who%20was%20mainly%20active%20in%20Andhra%20Pradesh%20from%20the%201980s%20until%20his%20death%20in%202009.%20In%20the%20nineties%2C%20he%20became%20increasingly%20critical%20of%20the%20People%E2%80%99s%20War%20Group%2C%20with%20which%20he%20had%20been%20associated%2C%20and%20developed%20those%20criticisms%20at%20length%20in%20a%20famous%20Telugu%20essay%20called%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Darker%20Side%20of%20the%20Naxalite%20Movement%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0(%3Ci%3ECheekati%20Konalu%3C%2Fi%3E).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%2016%20essays%20and%20articles%20in%20this%20collection%20straddle%20the%20period%20from%201985%20to%202003.%20Those%20were%20years%20that%20saw%20growing%20caste%20violence%20against%20the%20rural%20poor%2C%20strident%20middle-class%20campaigns%20against%20reservation%2C%20the%20consolidation%20of%20the%20Rashtriya%20Swayamsevak%20Sangh%20(RSS)%20as%20a%20mass%20political%20force%20working%20to%20transform%20India%20into%20a%20%E2%80%9CHindu%20state%E2%80%9D%2C%20and%20a%20steady%20increase%20in%20state%20authoritarianism.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20323px)%2085vw%2C%20323px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F10125153%2FScreenshot-2024-02-10-at-12.48.35-PM.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22323%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F10125153%2FScreenshot-2024-02-10-at-12.48.35-PM.png%20593w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F10125153%2FScreenshot-2024-02-10-at-12.48.35-PM-194x300.png%20194w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-696487%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22500%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EK.%20Balagopal%2C%20Understanding%20Fascism%3A%20Writings%20on%20Caste%2C%20Class%20and%20the%20State%2C%3Cbr%3ECurated%20and%20introduced%20by%20V.%20Geetha.%3Cbr%3ESouth%20Side%20Books%2C%20Hyderabad%20(2023).%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECaste%2C%20communalism%20and%20India%E2%80%99s%20increasingly%20authoritarian%20state%2C%20therefore%2C%20seem%20like%20the%20natural%20rubrics%20under%20which%20to%20organise%20the%20articles%20and%20this%20is%20what%20editor%20V.%20Geetha%20has%20done.%20With%20a%20final%20exception%2C%20Balagopal%E2%80%99s%20endorsement%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ECommunalism%20Combat%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20all%20of%20the%20articles%20were%20published%20in%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EEconomic%20and%20Political%20Weekly%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20pattern%20of%20caste%20violence%20described%20by%20Balagopal%20in%20the%20first%20two%20articles%20contains%20features%20which%20are%20worth%20highlighting%3A%20the%20atrocities%20occurred%20in%20the%20economically%20advanced%20coastal%20districts%20of%20Andhra%20where%20Kammas%20are%20the%20dominant%20agrarian%20community%3B%20the%20violence%20targeted%20Madigas%20and%20Malas%2C%20landless%20communities%20who%20work%20as%20farm%20servants%20and%20agricultural%20labourers%3B%20politically%2C%20the%20landed%20classes%20backed%20the%20Telugu%20Desam%20and%20its%20allies%20on%20the%20left%20and%20far%20right%2C%20while%20the%20Dalits%20supported%20Congress%20(I)%3B%20in%20Karamchedu%20in%20July%201985%20a%203000-strong%20mob%20of%20caste%20Hindus%20(viz.%20Kammas)%20assaulted%20the%20Madigas%20en%20masse%3B%20women%20were%20dragged%20out%20of%20their%20homes%2C%20stripped%20and%20molested%20or%20raped%3B%20at%20Chundur%20the%20police%20were%20%E2%80%9Cmute%20spectators%E2%80%9D%20to%20the%20massacre%20that%20occurred%20in%20August%201991%3B%20and%20most%20importantly%2C%20the%20Malas%20and%20Madigas%20of%20the%20coastal%20districts%20%E2%80%9Care%20better%20educated%2C%20assertive%20and%20identity-conscious%20than%20other%20Dalit%20communities%20there%20or%20elsewhere%E2%80%9D.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9C%5BT%5Dhe%20younger%20generation%20has%20started%20rejecting%20the%20social%20and%20political%20subordination%20to%20the%20forward%20castes%20that%20has%20traditionally%20been%20the%20lot%20of%20the%20Dalits%E2%80%A6It%20is%20this%E2%80%A6assertiveness%20of%20the%20Malas%20and%20Madigas%20that%20the%20forward%20castes%20find%20so%20intolerable%2C%20leading%20to%20assaults%20such%20as%20Karamchedu%20and%20Chundur%E2%80%9D%20(p.23).%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMoreover%2C%20by%20the%20%E2%80%9990s%20Balagopal%20had%20come%20around%20to%20the%20view%20that%20%E2%80%9Ctrying%20to%20convince%20the%20lower%20middle%20class%20and%20middle%20class%20savarna%20farmers%20that%20their%20material%20interest%20lies%20in%20a%20class%20unity%20with%20Dalits%2C%20is%20a%20fruitless%20and%20pedantic%20solution%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETurning%20to%20the%20issue%20of%20reservation%2C%20Balagopal%20surmised%20in%201986%20that%20well%20over%20half%20of%20Andhra%E2%80%99s%20population%20consisted%20of%20the%20so-called%20Backward%20Castes%20(BCs).%20So%20when%20a%20commission%20appointed%20in%201982%20eventually%20recommended%20that%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20backward%20caste%20reservation%20share%20should%20be%20raised%20from%2025%25%20to%2044%25%20(assuming%20that%208%25%20of%20those%20castes%20could%20fend%20for%20themselves%20in%20their%20competition%20with%20the%20forward%20castes)%2C%20this%20sparked%20outrage%20among%20the%20forward%20castes.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOf%20course%2C%20%E2%80%9Coutrage%E2%80%9D%20of%20this%20sort%20is%20never%20spontaneous%20and%20has%20to%20be%20contrived%20or%20conjured%2C%20and%20it%20was%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%20that%20used%20the%20anti-reservation%20campaigns%2C%20both%20here%20and%20in%20Gujarat%2C%20to%20build%20a%20base%20among%20the%20urban%20middle%20class.%20Students%20in%20the%20Akhil%20Bharatiya%20Vidya%20Parishad%20(ABVP)%20constituted%20the%20bulk%20of%20the%20anti-reservation%20agitators%20in%20Andhra%2C%20with%20their%20base%20in%20the%20medical%20and%20engineering%20colleges.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20landed%20upper%20caste%20families%20these%20students%20came%20from%20had%2C%20by%20now%20(mid%20eighties)%2C%20coalesced%20into%20a%20%E2%80%9Cnew%20rich%20Provincial%20Propertied%20Class%E2%80%9D.%20This%20new%20provincial%20bourgeoisie%20was%20far%20better%20organised%20than%20the%20backward%20castes%20because%20the%20forward%20castes%20of%20which%20it%20was%20made%20up%20were%20more%20widely%20spread%20across%20the%20state%20and%20used%20their%20extensive%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ecaste%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20links%20to%20mobilise%20their%20lower%20middle-class%20caste-fellows%20as%20the%20mass%20base%20of%20vociferous%20resistance%20to%20affirmative%20action.%20%E2%80%9CFoot%20soldiers%20of%20fascism%E2%80%9D%20was%20how%20Balagopal%20described%20the%20latter%20in%20probably%20his%20earliest%20reference%20to%20this.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFour%20years%20later%2C%20an%20article%20titled%20%3Cem%3EThis%20Anti-Mandal%20Mania%3C%2Fem%3E%20saw%20reservations%20as%20so%20threatening%20because%20they%20attacked%20the%20caste%20system.%20%E2%80%9CCaste%20is%20juridically%20dead%2C%20but%20very%20much%20alive%20politically%20and%20ideologically%E2%80%A6Tickets%20to%20the%20Assembly%20or%20Parliament%20at%20election%20time%2C%20public%20works%20and%20excise%20contracts%2C%20co-operative%20loans%2C%20industrial%20licenses%2C%20supply%20contracts%2C%20managerial%20jobs%20in%20the%20private%20sector%E2%80%A6not%20one%20of%20these%20is%20obtained%20without%20the%20use%20of%20caste%E2%80%9D%20(p.58).%20Caste%2C%20Balagopal%20argued%2C%20was%20a%20mode%20of%20reproduction%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20ruling%20class%2C%20an%20%E2%80%9Cunwritten%20reservation%20that%20the%20forward%20castes%20enjoy%20in%20the%20form%20of%20%E2%80%9Cconnections%E2%80%9D%E2%80%9D%20and%20incomparably%20more%20powerful%20than%20any%20of%20Mandal%E2%80%99s%20recommendations%20(p.59).%20But%20of%20course%20%E2%80%9C%5Bt%5Dhe%20casteism%20of%20the%20forward%20castes%20is%20never%20seen%20as%20casteism%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%20Balagopal%20used%20this%20analysis%20of%20the%20functionality%20of%20caste%20to%20the%20governance%20of%20class%20relations%20to%20defend%20the%20sort%20of%20identity%20politics%20that%20would%20emerge%20in%20the%201990s.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20remains%E2%80%A6the%20political%20duty%20of%20the%20poor%20and%20the%20deprived%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Eto%20use%20their%20caste%20identity%20in%20the%20struggle%20for%20their%20liberation%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9D.%20Caste%20and%20class%20struggles%20were%20%E2%80%9Cclosely%20interwoven%20and%20coterminous%20struggles%E2%80%9D%20(p.63).%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOf%20the%20five%20essays%20that%20confront%20%E2%80%9CHindutva%E2%80%9D%20in%20part%20two%20of%20the%20book%2C%20much%20of%20the%20focus%20is%20on%20the%20Indian%20lower-middle%20class.%20The%20cult%20of%20Ayyappa%2C%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20latest%20mass-god%20of%20Hinduism%E2%80%9D%2C%20was%20grounded%20socially%20in%20a%20growing%20lower%20middle%20class%20whose%20insecurities%2C%20Balagopal%20sensed%2C%20were%20fuelling%20all%20manner%20of%20reactions%2C%20from%20the%20proliferation%20of%20cults%20%E2%80%9Coutside%E2%80%9D%20the%20establishment%20to%20the%20rise%20of%20mafias%20and%20gangsterism%20in%20the%20towns.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBalagopal%20was%20a%20prescient%20writer%20and%20anticipated%20the%20way%20these%20various%20rebellions%20could%20be%20absorbed%20and%20reintegrated%20in%20the%20groundswell%20of%20what%20this%20article%20describes%20(in%201989)%20as%20%E2%80%9Cemerging%20fascist%20trends%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cdeveloping%20fascism%E2%80%9D.%20He%20referred%20to%20cults%20such%20as%20that%20at%20Sabarimalai%20being%20appropriated%20for%20%E2%80%9Ccommunal%20purposes%E2%80%9D%2C%20to%20the%20influx%20of%20agrarian%20wealth%20into%20Vijaywada%20creating%20a%20fertile%20basis%20for%20the%20operation%20of%20mafias%20in%20real%20estate%20and%20finance%2C%20and%20to%20the%20class%20hatred%20unleashed%20by%20the%20%E2%80%9Cvulgar%20new%20rich%20of%20coastal%20Andhra%E2%80%9D%2C%20with%20the%20trail%20of%20anti-Kamma%20violence%20left%20behind%20by%20riots%20in%20that%20port%20city.%20And%20the%20eighties%20saw%20a%20proliferation%20of%20repressive%20laws%20that%20only%20reinforced%20the%20%E2%80%9Cgradual%20demise%20of%20every%20one%20of%20the%20institutions%20of%20bourgeois%20democracy%E2%80%9D%20(p.93).%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBalagopal%E2%80%99s%201993%20piece%20on%20the%20demolition%20of%20the%20Babri%20Masjid%20is%20probably%20where%20his%20conception%20of%20the%20nature%20of%20Indian%20fascism%20comes%20through%20most%20clearly.%20This%20was%20where%20he%20argued%20that%20Hindutva%20%E2%80%9Chas%20its%20origin%20in%20a%20political%20need%20to%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ecounter%20aspirations%20for%20democracy%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9D%20.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EIts%20mass%20base%20was%20constructed%20out%20of%20the%20%E2%80%9Cresentment%20and%20frustration%20born%20in%20reaction%20to%20the%20space%20conquered%20by%20the%20oppressed%20and%20the%20underprivileged%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20political%20universe%E2%80%9D.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAlthough%20he%20insisted%20that%20there%20was%20no%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Erevolution%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20going%20on%20in%20India%20to%20warrant%20describing%20Hindutva%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Ccounter-revolution%E2%80%9D%2C%20he%20pointed%20out%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthere%20has%20been%20a%20tremendous%20expansion%20of%20democratic%20and%20egalitarian%20aspirations%20among%20the%20oppressed%20people%E2%80%9D.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20if%20democracy%E2%80%99s%20right%20arm%20was%20fettered%20to%20a%20state%20apparatus%20that%20thrived%20on%20a%20culture%20of%20repression%2C%20its%20constitutional%20left%20arm%20allowed%20for%20a%20culture%20of%20freedom%20that%20nurtured%20aspirations%20for%20equality%2C%20justice%20and%20self-respect%20among%20the%20mass%20of%20working%20people.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIf%20Hindutva%20was%20nonetheless%20capable%20of%20attracting%20%E2%80%9Csignificant%20support%E2%80%9D%20at%20the%20%E2%80%9Cmiddle%20and%20lower%20levels%20of%20society%E2%80%9D%2C%20this%2C%20Balagopal%20suggested%2C%20was%20because%20society%20was%20characterised%20by%20a%20pervasive%20sense%20of%20hierarchy%20more%20than%20it%20was%20by%20any%20simple%20bipolarity%2C%20for%20example%2C%20%E2%80%9C%5BT%5Dhe%20smallest%20farmer%20thinks%20he%20is%20superior%20to%20the%20wage%20labourer%E2%80%9D%2C%20and%20the%20BJP%20was%20adept%20at%20making%20this%20sense%20of%20hierarchy%20(recursive%20inequalities)%20a%20source%20of%20resentment%20at%20the%20alleged%20%E2%80%9Cpampering%E2%80%9D%20of%20workers%2C%20women%2C%20untouchables%2C%20Muslims%20and%20so%20on.%20Whatever%20one%20thinks%20of%20this%20explanation%2C%20by%202002%20it%20was%20not%20resentment%20but%20outright%20hatred%20that%20loomed%20large%20in%20Balaglopal%E2%80%99s%20analysis%20of%20communalism.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%E2%80%9CThe%20common%20Hindu%E2%80%99s%20hatred%20for%20anything%20to%20do%20with%20Muslims%E2%80%A6is%20the%20only%20thing%20alive%20in%20Gujarat%20today%E2%80%9D%2C%20he%20wrote%20in%20June%20that%20year.%20Indeed%2C%20%E2%80%9Ca%20very%20large%20number%20of%20Hindus%20all%20over%20the%20country%20harbour%20an%20extraordinary%20hatred%20for%20Muslims%E2%80%9D.%20Balagopal%E2%80%99s%20reflections%20on%20the%20ghastly%20pogroms%20that%20tore%20through%20Gujarat%20in%202002%20are%20an%20extraordinary%20piece%20of%20writing%20%E2%80%93%20not%20just%20for%20the%20rawness%20of%20the%20emotion%20expressed%20there%20but%20because%2C%20to%20his%20credit%2C%20he%20was%20willing%20to%20confront%20what%20he%20called%20%E2%80%9Cuncomfortable%20questions%E2%80%9D.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20participation%20of%20Adivasis%20and%20Dalits%20in%20the%20rioting%2C%20looting%20and%20killing%20is%20one%20such%20%5Bquestion%5D%E2%80%A6In%20all%20the%20areas%20along%20the%20north-eastern%20border%20of%20the%20State%E2%80%A6there%20was%20sizeable%20participation%20of%20Adivasis%20along%20with%20non-Adivasis%20in%20the%20violence.%20The%20two%20were%20part%20of%20the%20same%20mob%20in%20most%20cases%E2%80%9D.%20So%20too%20with%20Dalits.%20%E2%80%9CDalit%20participation%20in%20the%20violence%20at%20Ahmedabad%20is%20even%20less%20ambiguous.%20A%20large%20number%20of%20Dalit%20youth%20took%20direct%20part%20in%20the%20gruesome%20violence%20of%20that%20city%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%20This%20was%20a%20frontal%20challenge%20to%20the%20unrestrained%20defence%20of%20identity%20politics%20he%20had%20advocated%20as%20late%20as%201990%2C%20and%20to%20essentialist%20constructions%20of%20%E2%80%9Cthe%E2%80%9D%20Advasi%20and%20%E2%80%9Cthe%E2%80%9D%20Dalit.%20The%20manipulation%20of%20identities%20is%20of%20course%20the%20heart%20of%20fascist%20politics%20and%20Balagopal%20knew%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9Cparticipation%E2%80%9D%20of%20these%20communities%20in%20the%20pogroms%20had%20everything%20to%20do%20with%20the%20organising%20drives%20of%20the%20Sangh%20parivar.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20Vanavasi%20Kalyan%20Samiti%20of%20the%20Vishwa%20Hindu%20Parishad%20has%20made%20considerable%20inroads%20into%20the%20Adivasi%20areas%E2%80%A6every%20Adivasi%20village%20has%20at%20least%20one%20VHP%20activist%E2%80%9D.%20The%20Adivasis%20are%20%E2%80%9Cmade%20to%20feel%20that%20they%20are%20Hindus%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20collection%20ends%20with%20Balagopal%E2%80%99s%20scathing%20critique%20of%20the%20ineluctable%20ways%20in%20which%20the%20once%20beating%20heart%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20democracy%20has%20been%20progressively%20stifled%20by%20a%20slew%20of%20laws%20and%20repressive%20practices%20that%20have%20systematically%20undermined%20the%20rights%20of%20individuals%20under%20the%20Indian%20constitution.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20terror%20emanating%20from%20minorities%20alone%20is%20depicted%20as%20terror%E2%80%9D%2C%20he%20wrote%20about%20both%20TADA%20and%20the%20Law%20Commission%E2%80%99s%20replication%20of%20its%20political%20and%20communal%20biases.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESo%20how%20do%20we%20blend%20these%20different%20strands%20of%20the%20argument%20into%20a%20coherent%20idea%20of%20Indian%20fascism%3F%20The%20conception%20that%20best%20captures%20what%20Balagopal%20was%20driving%20at%20is%20Marcuse%E2%80%99s%20notion%20of%20fascism%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Cpreventive%20counterrevolution%E2%80%9D.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.versobooks.com%2Fen-gb%2Fproducts%2F2627-late-fascism%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EAlberto%20Toscano%20has%20foregrounded%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3Ethis%20in%20a%20fascinating%20chapter%20of%20his%20recent%20book%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ELate%20Fascism%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E(Verso%2C%202023).%20All%20of%20the%20moments%20that%20Marcuse%20listed%20in%20a%201970%20interview%20with%20Hans%20Magnus%20Enzensberger%20as%20markers%20of%20an%20incipient%20fascism%20in%20the%20US%20%E2%80%93%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20gradual%20or%20rapid%20abolition%20of%20the%20remnants%20of%20the%20constitutional%20state%E2%80%A6granting%20the%20police%20extraordinary%20legal%20powers%E2%80%A6the%20court%20decisions%20of%20recent%20years%E2%80%9D%2C%20and%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20almost%20direct%20censorship%20of%20the%20press%2C%20television%20and%20radio%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20all%20of%20these%20have%20been%20pivotal%20moments%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20political%20transformation%20since%20the%201980s.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20point%20of%20this%20unlikely%20comparison%20is%20not%20the%20analogy%2C%20but%20the%20insight%20it%20offers%20in%20suggesting%20that%20like%20the%20US%20(or%20Israel%20for%20that%20matter)%2C%20India%20has%20its%20own%20version(s)%20of%20%E2%80%9Cracialised%20state%20terror%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0and%20this%20or%20these%20versions%20is%20where%20we%20have%20to%20start%20in%20trying%20to%20%E2%80%9Cunderstand%20fascism%E2%80%9D%20in%20India.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EViewed%20in%20this%20light%2C%20Balagopal%E2%80%99s%20essays%20and%20the%20editor%E2%80%99s%20work%20in%20putting%20them%20together%20in%20this%20way%20become%20seminal%20contributions%20to%20grasping%20the%20nature%20of%20fascism%20in%20India.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3EJairus%C2%A0Banaji%20is%20with%20the%20Department%20of%20Development%20Studies%2C%20SOAS%2C%20University%20of%20London.%20His%20most%20recent%20book%20is%20called%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cspan%3EWanting%20Something%20Completely%20Different%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0(Rab-Rab%2C%20Helsinki%2C%202023).%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707550084000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F30123722%2FIllustration-Pariplab-Chakraborty.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fk-balagopals-incisive-